20209040.review:
The first 9 hours from that game went unnoticed for me. I could finish only one adventure. And in these 9 hours i have tried 5 heroes (from 20). Which means that it is a very good value for money. 

The game advantages:
- the game theme is chosen well;
- the game mechanics are very good. They have teached me variuos things about the real life, believe it or not;
- a single game is not too lenghty. Because of the replayability factor that is a good sign;
- the graphics and the sounds are good;
- practically bug-free;
- the game is highly replayable;
- authentic in-game locations;
- the RNG is very well done. That means that the combat is very, very "controllable". Which means that there is RNG involved, but it is restricted to certain game mechanics, which on its side are so designed, that they reward and not punish, the player, if played right, of course. The RNG on the area map is very nice, too. Because it adds to the replayability factor;

The bad:
- the game is highly addictive :D;

To the game developers:
i will pay for additional exploration maps. Especially, if they are themed after South American, more Asian, or more African locations. If you can widen the game volume in some other way, without compromising the game mechanics, i will pay for that, too.
